cyclone.name: FRED
cyclone.current_location: about 125 mi (200 km) SSW of Great Exuma Island
cyclone.trajectory: moving WNW across eastern-central Cuba, forecast to turn NW toward the Florida Keys on Saturday, then track northward just offshore the Florida west coast and inland over the Florida Panhandle/Alabama early next week
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: Florida Panhandle or Big Bend coast

weather_observation.watch_coast: Southwest coast of Florida from Englewood south and east to Ocean Reef; several Cuban provinces
weather_observation.warning_coast: Florida Keys west of Ocean Reef to Dry Tortugas and Florida Bay
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Cuba, Bahamas, Florida Keys, Florida west coast, northern Gulf Coast (FL Panhandle to AL)
weather_observation.wind: Breezy conditions possible mid-week (gusts 20–30 mph) as remnant low passes inland well to the west
weather_observation.storm_surge: None expected along Delaware Bay/coast because system remains inland before exiting to the Atlantic north of the Mid-Atlantic region
weather_observation.rainfall: Remnant moisture could bring 1–2 inches of rain 17–18 Aug, locally higher in thunderstorms
weather_observation.other_hazards: Minor river/urban ponding possible if localized downpours occur, but no significant marine or port operational hazards anticipated
